 Nation at a Glance

 Schoolteacher shot by student

 Basti (PTI): A schoolteacher who complained about a students behaviour to his parents was allegedly shot dead by him on Saturday, Uttar Pradesh police said.

 Chandra Bhanu Pandey, a teacher at the Saraswati Shishu Mandir, was shot dead by his student Dhirendra Yadav after he visited the students home in Avas Vikas colony, the police said.

 Yadav used a hand-made weapon to shoot Pandey while he was returning after meeting his parents. The teacher died on the way to hospital.

 Angry teachers and students staged a sit-in at the hospital crossing, demanding Yadavs arrest. Markets in some areas were shut down in protest and vehicular traffic was disrupted.

 An FIR has been filed against Yadav and investigations are on, the police said.

 US plastic waste to go back

 Kochi (PTI): Customs authorities have 

 ordered a Secunderabad-based firm, which imported about 

 250 tonnes of plastic scrap from the US, to ship it back 

 and imposed a fine of Rs 10,000.

 The consignment was imported as plastic PET bottles in 12 containers from Virginia in August this year. But on examination, customs authorities found it was assorted plastic scrap, which is banned in the country.

 The importer, Trans Asia Global Trades, will also have to pay a penalty of Rs 25,000 to get the consignment released from the customs authorities.

 According to the hazardous waste handling and management rules, such materials cannot be imported into the country, customs joint commissioner Satish Reddy said.

 Housing scam

 New Delhi (PTI): The CBI has filed an 

 FIR against N. Diwakar, former registrar of cooperatives 

 societies, and nine others in connection with the Rs 4,000-crore 

 cooperative scam in Delhi.

 Forged documents were allegedly used to revive the defunct Gautam Cooperative Group Housing Society in South Delhi.

 Geelani on Haj

 Srinagar (PTI): Hardline Hurriyat chairman 

 Syed Ali Shah Geelani was among 413 pilgrims who left for 

 Mecca on Saturday to perform Haj, official sources said. 

 Geelani, who had accused authorities of denying him permission 

 to visit the holy city for the last five years, left with 

 his wife.

